{
    "@context" : "https://schema.org/",
    "@type" : "JobPosting",
    "title" : "Technical Product Manager",
    "description" : "As the <b>Technical Product Manager</b> for the Core Platform at Dynamo.ai, you will be responsible for steering the vision, strategy, and execution of our platform's infrastructure and deployment capabilities. This is a hands-on, high-impact role that requires deep technical expertise, a strong understanding of platform engineering, and excellent stakeholder management skills.You will collaborate closely with engineering, compliance, and customer success teams to ensure that Dynamo.ai’s platform meets customer requirements, handles demanding performance metrics, and maintains industry-leading standards of security, scalability, and usability.
<h3>Responsibilities</h3>
<ul>
<li> Below are the Responsibilities for the Technical Product Manager Role: </li><br><b>1. Platform Deployment as a PaaS (Platform as a Service)</b><li>Define and prioritize technical requirements to ensure the <a>Dynamo.ai</a> product can be deployed seamlessly in customer environments (e.g., VPCs, on-premises physical servers) as a scalable PaaS offering.</li><li>Collaborate with engineering teams to optimize Kubernetes-based deployment pipelines to support high throughput and ultra-low latency.</li><li>Work with DevOps and infrastructure engineers to enhance platform stability and ensure robust CI/CD practices for customer environments.</li><br><b>2. Security and Compliance</b><li>Ensure the platform aligns with industry standards such as SOC2, ISO 27001, and customer-specific compliance needs.</li><li>Drive the implementation of robust Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) systems, encryption protocols, and other security features.</li><li>Partner with security teams to develop and execute audits, penetration testing, and ongoing compliance validation.</li><br><b>3. Documentation and Self-Installation Enablement</b><li>Lead the creation of detailed, user-friendly documentation and installation guides to empower customers to independently deploy and manage <a>Dynamo.ai</a>’s platform.</li><li>Collect feedback from customers to continuously improve the self-installation process and reduce dependency on <a>Dynamo.ai</a>’s technical support.</li><br><b>4. SaaS Platform Scalability and Robustness</b><li>Oversee initiatives to ensure the SaaS offering can scale efficiently to handle large numbers of customer users without compromising performance.</li><li>Identify potential bottlenecks in the SaaS architecture and collaborate with engineers to address them proactively.</li><br><b>5. System Validation and Error Messaging</b><li>Define and implement validation testing strategies to ensure the platform is resilient when deployed in diverse customer environments.</li><li>Work with engineering teams to create clear, actionable error messages that improve troubleshooting and system reliability.</li></ul>
