{
    "@context" : "https://schema.org/",
    "@type" : "JobPosting",
    "title" : "Tech Sales",
    "description" : "<h3>Description</h3>
<p>vHive is seeking a dynamic and technically skilled individual to occupy a <strong>Tech Sales </strong>position. This role will help grow and support strategic customer accounts. This role is ideal for someone who combines strong sales capabilities with a hands-on understanding of drone technology and SaaS platforms. You will play a key role in expanding customer usage, adoption, and satisfaction while directly contributing to account growth and long-term partnership success.</p><p>You will serve as a trusted advisor, engaging directly with customers at both executive and operational levels. Your ability to educate, inspire, and provide technical value will make you the go-to resource for your accounts.</p><p>vHive is seeking a dynamic and technically skilled individual to occupy a <strong>Tech Sales </strong>position. This role will help grow and support a US based strategic customer account. This role is ideal for someone who combines strong sales capabilities with a hands-on understanding of technology and SaaS platforms. You will play a key role in expanding customer usage, adoption, and satisfaction while directly contributing to account growth and long-term partnership success.</p><p>You will serve as a trusted advisor, engaging directly with customers at both executive and operational levels. Your ability to educate, inspire, and provide technical value will make you the go-to resource for your accounts.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Build deep, trust-based relationships with existing enterprise customers by actively supporting account strategy and showcasing new capabilities</li><li>Deliver engaging technical product demonstrations and training sessions for both executives and end users, in person and remotely</li><li>Own and maintain customer education resources, including the vHive knowledge base and branded video tutorials</li><li>Lead onboarding and ongoing training sessions, ensuring customers are maximizing value from the vHive platform and drone workflows</li><li>Conduct regular check-ins and calls with customers to promote adoption, address issues, and uncover new opportunities</li><li>Proactively drive usage of all platform features and ensure proper integration with the customer's existing systems</li><li>Represent the customer internally, collaborating with Sales, Product, and R&amp;D to advocate for feature requests and improvements</li><li>Travel as needed to support relationship building, training, and demonstrations in the field</li></ul><p><strong>Current Key Tasks</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee the quality and relevance of all customer training materials and content</li><li>Serve as a subject matter expert for power users and executive stakeholders</li><li>Act as a bridge between customer feedback and internal product improvements</li><li>Build new workflows and standard operating procedures</li></ul>
<h3>Requirements</h3>
<ul><li>5 years of proven experience in technical sales or similar roles, technical account management, preferably within large enterprise environments delivering SaaS solutions</li><li>Recent experience in the telecom sector is highly preferred</li><li>Deep understanding of organizational dynamics and customer engagement strategies</li><li>Comfortable operating in a global, matrixed organization and handling complex business scenarios with professionalism</li><li>Track record of achieving growth and success targets through customer relationship management</li><li>Strong interpersonal and communication skills, both written and verbal</li><li>Technical knowledge of drone systems and software is required</li><li>Fluent English (spoken and written)</li><li>Resume must be submitted in English</li><li>Location: Mexico, Dallas, or Minnesota</li><li>Ability to travel up to 25% of the time</li></ul>
<h3>Nice to have</h3>
<p><strong>Preferred Skills and Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Familiarity with <strong>SaaS platforms</strong>, particularly in roles involving customer implementation, usage expansion, or technical support</li><li>Experience working with or selling into <strong>telecom carriers</strong> or <strong>network operators</strong>, with an understanding of industry-specific challenges, infrastructure, and operational needs</li><li>Ability to communicate technical concepts related to drone data capture, modeling accuracy, and platform capabilities in a clear and engaging way</li><li>Background in technical sales, solutions engineering, or customer success within a drone technology or geospatial analytics company is a plus</li><li>Knowledge of integration between drone data and enterprise asset management or network planning systems is an advantage</li><li>Hands-on experience with <strong>UAS (Unmanned Aerial Systems)</strong>, including flight operations, mission planning, and hardware troubleshooting</li></ul><p>Strong understanding of <strong>photogrammetry</strong> principles and workflows, including the generation and interpretation of <strong>3D models</strong>, digital twins, and point clouds</p>",
