{
    "@context" : "https://schema.org/",
    "@type" : "JobPosting",
    "title" : "Senior Product Manager – AI for Retail",
    "description" : "<p>NVIDIA is the defining technology company of the Artificial Intelligence era. Our unique legacy of innovation is powered by extraordinary technology—and outstanding people! We’re seeking a Senior Product Manager to drive the vision, development, and launch of innovative AI blueprints and reference workflows that leverage the power of NVIDIA's AI and accelerated computing for the retail, consumer packaged goods (CPG), and quick service restaurant (QSR) industries.</p><p>Seeking a multifaceted product leader comfortable in fast-paced settings, adapting to changing needs, and passionate about crafting AI's future. You will collaborate closely with cross-functional teams, including engineering, solution architects, marketing, and sales, to ensure the successful design, execution, and market adoption of the retail AI offerings. This position offers an opportunity to drive groundbreaking work at the intersection of AI and retail, helping to transform the industry.</p><p><b>What you'll be doing:</b></p><ul><li><p>Gain Expertise - Keep pace with NVIDIA AI innovations, industry technology changes, new research, partner and competitor innovation. Everyone has a different learning style. Whether its rapid prototyping, talking to experts, or hands-on-keyboard development and test, we will support your self-directed learning.<br>Design and Build- Author compelling product requirements that showcase the art of what’s possible for our retail, CPG and QSR industries while showcasing NVIDIA AI solutions. Work cross functionally to support the development of AI blueprints and reference workflows. This will require you to be hands-on, understanding the underlying functionality, testing and provide feedback for improvements or new functionality.</p></li><li><p>Launch Products – Support the go-to-market strategy and cross-functional implementation of the plan across Marketing, PR, Sales, etc. including creation of technical content for blog posts, webinars, developer tutorials, and more to communicate the product value proposition.</p></li><li><p>Delight the Market - Ensure the developer experience for retail blueprints and workflows. They should be a delight to use for any retail developer – from documentation to ease of install to customization and deployment. Support partners looking to use blueprints and support early adopters through Early Access programs. Work closely with customers and partners to understand product quality and monitor critical bugs.</p></li><li><p>Be an Authority - We want you to become a recognized authority within and outside of NVIDIA! You can do this by publishing content, giving presentations, or engaging directly with communities.</p></li></ul><p><b>What we need to see:</b></p><ul><li><p>BS or MS in Data Science, Computer Science, or equivalent experience.</p></li><li><p>12+ overall years of combined experience in product management, data science, software development, &amp;/or ML ops.</p></li><li><p>Significant experience in a technical product leadership role at a technology or retail/CPG company.</p></li><li><p>Excellent balance of industry knowledge and experience with AI technologies and approaches such as generative and agentic AI, computer vision and digital twin simulation.</p></li><li><p>Analytical approach and ability to synthesize the latest research, engineering feasibility, and market trends into product strategy.</p></li><li><p>Outstanding communication skills with demonstrated ability to articulate a value proposition to technical and non-technical audiences.</p></li><li><p>Experience working cross functionally with engineering, research, developer relations, and go-to-market teams.</p></li><li><p>Ability to drive concurrent projects and priorities in a dynamic environment.</p></li></ul><p><b>Ways to stand out from the crowd:</b></p><ul><li><p>Experience in retail or CPG industries with deep knowledge of retail AI development and deployment workflows, for both edge and cloud.</p></li><li><p>Experience with NVIDIA technologies, tools, and software such as NeMo microservices and NIMs.</p></li><li><p>Hands-on experience building or using generative AI solutions.<br> </p></li></ul><p>If you are a self-starter with a blend of market, technical and product skills, and a passion for groundbreaking generative AI technology please apply today!</p><p><span>NVIDIA is widely considered one of the technology world’s most desirable employers. We have some of the world's most forward-thinking and hardworking people on our team. If you're creative and autonomous, we want to hear from you!</span></p>The base salary range is 208,000 USD - 379,500 USD. Your base salary will be determined based on your location, experience, and the pay of employees in similar positions.<p><span>You will also be eligible for equity and <a>benefits</a>. </span><span><span>NVIDIA accepts applications on an ongoing basis.</span><span> </span></span></p>NVIDIA is committed to fostering a diverse work environment and proud to be an equal opportunity employer. As we highly value diversity in our current and future employees, we do not discriminate (including in our hiring and promotion practices) on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, disability status or any other characteristic protected by law.",
