{
    "@context" : "https://schema.org/",
    "@type" : "JobPosting",
    "title" : "Principal Applied Scientist- Office AI Platform team",
    "description" : "<p><span><span><span>Microsoft 365 Copilot is a groundbreaking productivity tool that </span><span>leverages</span><span> the power of large language models, user data, Microsoft Graph, and the web to drive unparalleled creativity and productivity. At the heart of this innovation is the </span></span><strong><span><span>Office AI Platform team</span></span></strong><span><span>, which plays a crucial role in the aid of development of Copilot experiences in Office apps like Word, Excel, and PowerPoint and </span><span>assists</span><span> teams across Microsoft. </span></span><strong><span><span>We own the infrastructure and base AI platform that enables complex orchestration of Copilot workflows to put powerful AI capabilities at the user’s fingertips.   </span></span></strong><span> </span></span></p><p><span><span><span>We </span><span>leverage</span><span> the most advanced, large language models (LLMs) to develop </span><span>cutting-edge</span><span> Copilot experiences. We are hands-on, </span><span>assist</span><span> our partner teams in their Machine Learning (ML) efforts and set guidance on best practices through detailed experimentation and research. We have important AI skills like P</span><span>o</span><span>werPoint Summary, Q&amp;A, Podcast generation, among others. We have shipped the first fine-tuned model for M365 and are working on multiple fine-tuning scenarios for o3, CUA, and others.  </span></span><span> </span></span></p><p><span><span><span>We are </span><span>seeking</span><span> a highly motivated and experienced scientist with </span><span>expertise</span><span> in machine learning. As a </span></span><strong><span><span>Principal Applied Scientist</span><span> </span></span></strong><span><span>in </span></span><strong><span><span>Office AI, </span></span></strong><span><span>you will work in an exciting and fast-paced environment, collaborating closely with teams across the company, including Microsoft Research and various product groups. You will work as part of an organization that brings together talent in the areas of large language models, deep learning, information retrieval, software engineering, and responsible AI. We value and encourage Inclusivity in the belief that it leads to both great workplaces and great products.</span></span><span> </span></span></p><p><span>Microsoft’s mission is to empower every person and every organization on the planet to achieve more. As employees we come together with a growth mindset, innovate to empower others, and collaborate to realize our shared goals. Each day we build on our values of respect, integrity, and accountability to create a culture of inclusion where everyone can thrive at work and beyond.</span></p>
<h3>Responsibilities</h3>
